#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:7
msgid "Software vulnerabilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:9
msgid ""
"Security issues with system software installed on machines mainly rely on"
" the NixOS security process for mitigations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:12
msgid ""
"When mitigating a vulnerability we may choose different strategies "
"depending on the situation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:15
msgid ""
"Ideally we will update the package to an unaffected version that stays "
"API compatible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:17
msgid ""
"We may update to a package with API incompatibility but will help our "
"customers to fix breakage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:19
msgid ""
"We may stay on the existing version and include a patch provided by the "
"vendor, security researchers, other distributions or other sources we "
"deem trustworthy after a review."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:22
msgid ""
"We may contain the effect of the vulnerability by disabling features, "
"adjusting configuration, firewalling or other measures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:24
msgid ""
"We may choose to ignore the security vulnerability if the impact or "
"attack vectors are not relevant on our platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:26
msgid "We might take other actions not listed here, depending on the situation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:28
msgid "NixOS 22.11 (upcoming)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:30
msgid ""
"This is the currently actively maintained NixOS release that receives "
"timely security updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:33
msgid ""
"We update our platform with security updates every 2 weeks, but may "
"update intermittently if high risk vulnerabilities become known."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:36
msgid "NixOS 22.05 (current)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:38
msgid ""
"The NixOS community has stopped support for this distribution but we "
"monitor security updates received on the 22.11 branch for potential "
"backports in high risk situations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:42
msgid "NixOS 21.11 and older (outdated)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:44
msgid ""
"No security updates are provided. Customers in need of guaranteed "
"security updates are advised to update to NixOS 22.05"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:47
msgid "Gentoo (outdated)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/software-vulnerabilities.md:49
msgid ""
"We provide selective security updates by reviewing the published list of "
"Gentoo Linux Security Advisories (GLSA) every 2 months and selecting "
"critical security updates where necessary."
msgstr ""

